:: Gwylan Request
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $gwylan.requestDone>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>"I-is there anything else I can do?" you ask.
		<<case "bratty">>"Do you have anything else for me to do?" you ask.
		<<default>>"Is there anything else I can help with?" you ask.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> tilts <<his>> head at you. "I appreciate the offer, but <span class="green">I already owe you</span>." <<He>> giggles. "Be careful. If you're this eager to help, I might start to take advantage."
<<elseif $gwylan.request.event>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>"I-is there anything else I can do?" you ask.
		<<case "bratty">>"Do you have anything else for me to do?" you ask.
		<<default>>"Is there anything else I can help with?" you ask.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> tilts <<his>> head at you. "You still haven't done what I already asked of you." <<He>> pats the top of your head. "One thing at a time, dear."
<<elseif $daily.gwylan.request and !$gwylanSeen.includesAny("caught", "caught_no_lewd") and ["clothing"].includes($gwylan.requestLast?.event)>>
	/* Prevent players from repeatedly skipping trigger for final snooping event */
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>"I-is there anything else I can do?" you ask.
		<<case "bratty">>"Do you have anything else for me to do?" you ask.
		<<default>>"Is there anything else I can help with?" you ask.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> tilts <<his>> head at you. "I appreciate the offer, but if you keep this up I'm afraid you'll develop feelings for me, dear. Come back tomorrow if you're so eager."
<<elseif !$gwylanSeen.includes("request_intro")>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>"I-is there anything I can help with?" you ask.
		<<case "bratty">>"Hey, you look busy. Do you need anything?" you ask.
		<<default>>"Is there anything I can help with?" you ask.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<if _gwylanStatus.includes("cautious")>>
		<<He>> crosses <<his>> arms and looks sceptical. "What makes you want to help me?" <<He>> seems to realise something, and <<his>> expression quickly changes. "I'm sorry, that was rude of me. I could always use an extra pair of hands and eyes. Usually in my garden, but that's off-limits."
	<<else>>
		"You want to... help?" <<he>> asks, putting a hand under <<his>> chin. "I could always use an extra pair of hands and eyes. Usually in my garden, but that's off-limits."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	After a moment of thought, <<he>> snaps <<his>> fingers.
	<<run gwylanRequest("tutorial")>>
	<<gwylanRequestText>>
<<else>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>"I-is there anything I can help with?" you ask.
		<<case "bratty">>"Hey, you look busy. Do you need anything?" you ask.
		<<default>>"Is there anything I can help with?" you ask.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	"Yes, actually," <<he>> says with a smile.
	<<run gwylanRequest()>>
	<<gwylanRequestText>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Request Tutorial Complete
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
You hand Gwylan the wolfshrooms.
<br><br>

<<set _amountToRemove to 3 - $gwylanTutorialShrooms>>
<<if $plants.wolfshroom.amount>>
	<<set $plants.wolfshroom.amount -= _amountToRemove>>
<</if>>
<<unset $gwylanTutorialShrooms>>
/* Above is in case the player became proficient enough in tending to pick wolfshrooms without the tutorial exception half way through */

<<He>> turns them over in <<his>> hands.
<<if currentSkillValue('tending') lt 300>>
	"Not the finest quality. Small, and this one's almost inert. You broke a few bits off when pulling them up, and the caps are warped too. Not bad, though. I'm sure you'll learn how to find better specimens in due time."
<<else>>
	"Very nice. You've got a good eye. These will work well."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> holds one up to the light. "They were thought to boost strength and virility, while imparting the spirit of the wolf, and that myth still persists. It's an understandable mistake to make considering their true effects.
Wolfshrooms are aphrodisiacs and suppress fear responses. Consuming them certainly makes one more brave, and could enable feats one might not normally be capable of because of that. They also promote the growth of body hair."
<br><br>

<<He>> smiles at you. "Thank you. If you're still in the mood to help, I might have more for you to do. But, I need to pay you back first."
<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("request_tutorial")>>
<br><br>

<span class="gold">You can now complete tasks for Gwylan in exchange for services. More may become available as you tell <<him>> your stories.</span>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Request Clothes Complete
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

<<if $gwylan.request.special is "gas mask">>
	<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("request_gas_mask")>>
	Gwylan gently brushes <<his>> fingers against your cheek. You shiver, though you can't feel <<his>> touch through the thick rubber of your gas mask.
	<<He>> stares at you through the tinted lenses, <<his>> gaze stripping you bare.
	<br><br>

	When <<he>> speaks, <<his>> voice is quiet. "Every man, woman, and child in the country received one of these in the second World War.
	After the chemical warfare of the first, the government feared that civilians would be on the receiving end of it. Special masks were made for the littlest ones.
	Gas drills were held in schools, and posters were hung as a reminder to all: always carry your gas mask with you. They were fined if they were caught without one."
	<<He>> lowers <<his>> hand. "Fortunately, they were never needed. Unfortunately, the masks were made with asbestos fibers, leaving many with long-term health consequences.
	Sometimes decisions made with the best intentions do more harm than good. Sometimes the one devoted to protecting you is the one to kill you in the end." <<gghistory>><<historyskill 12>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> gives you a wry smile. "I doubt this replica is in any way dangerous, but still, I'd like to have it." It's not a choice.
	<<He>> reaches for the straps securing your mask and carefully removes it. "Thank you for humouring an old soul's request. What can I do for you?"
	<<faceruined true>>
	<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
	<br><br>

	<<gwylanOptions>>
<<elseif $gwylan.request.special is "gold accessories">>
	<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("request_gold_accessories")>>
	Gwylan gently lifts your wrist, examining one of your gold bracelets. <<He>> then lifts the other, and holds your wrists together.
	"Iron and silver were often used as restraints, but gold had its place in that too. One shackled by gold is thought to be bound to the earth itself by greed, obsession, or yearning for something that was lost."
	<<He>> adjusts <<his>> grip and runs <<his>> fingers up your forearms, making your hands relax.
	<br><br>

	"In alchemy, gold was the symbol of purity and perfection. Its symbol was a simple circle with a dot in the middle, to represent the sun. A closed loop.
	Many a rich and powerful individual spent their fortunes on attempting to discover the art of chrysopoeia, or transmutation of base metals to gold, most commonly lead.
	The symbol of a snake devouring its own tail is often associated with the art. Another closed loop."
	<br><br>

	With a deft touch, <<he>> slips the bracelets off over your hands. <<He>> holds one in between you, looking at you through it with one eye. A dot within a circle. You feel profoundly exposed. <<stress 2>><<gstress>>
	<br><br>

	"Gold is soft enough to eat and biologically inert, and was often powdered and used as a food decoration thought to halt aging. It was worn to make one's skin vibrant and youthful.
	Even today, some believe infusions of gold into the skin keep the ravages of time at bay. Another metal that was thought to have this property was mercury sulfide, also called cinnabar.
	Related to the philosopher's stone, a mythical object capable of the aforementioned transmutation of metals. In reality, it was simply poison, and any who imbibed it met a slow, painful end."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> leans under the counter and grabs a small chisel. <<He>> gouges one of the bracelets with it, and looks closer.
	"As expected, these aren't gold all the way through. It's merely copper plated with gold. Are you noticing a pattern?
	In a way, we're still trying to transmute base metals. We're still binding ourselves with gilded shackles for vanity, and some still continue to drink poison in an effort to extend their life." <<ggscience>><<scienceskill 12>>
	<br><br>

	<<specialClothesUnlock "set" "jasper">><<set $daily.gwylan.jasper to true>>

	<<He>> holds out <<his>> hands, and you give <<him>> the <<if $worn.neck.name isnot "familiar collar">>choker and<</if>> anklets too. "I can still make use of these. Thank you for the lovely gifts. Now, what can I do to return the favour?"
	<<handsruined true>><<neckruined true>><<legsruined true>>
	<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
	<br><br>

	<<gwylanOptions>>
<<else>>
	<<set _clothesToTake to []>>
	<<set _clothesToTakeText to []>>
	<<run $gwylan.request.items.filter(item => item.name === V.worn[item.slot].name).forEach(item => {
		T.clothesToTake.pushUnique(item.slot);
		T.clothesToTakeText.push(item.name);
	})>>

	<<switch $gwylan.request.special>>
		<<case "maid">>
			Gwylan walks around you, inspecting your $worn.upper.name.
			"A bit tight around the waist to accentuate curves, but comfortable enough for extended periods of service. Holds dust well, to prevent it from getting on the floor after cleaning.
			The maid drags the dirt and dust home with them, to do even more cleaning."
			<br><br>

			<<if $worn.upper.name is "traditional maid dress">>
				<<He>> crouches down, inspecting the lower half. "Thick apron all the way down, in anticipation of spills." <<He>> fleeces it down. "Good material."
			<<elseif $worn.upper.name is "Victorian maid dress">>
				<<He>> crouches down, inspecting the lower half. "An imitation of a much older style, but rugged." <<He>> fleeces it down. "The design is timeless."
			<<else>>
				<<He>> crouches down, inspecting the lower half. "A more modern design, more frilly than some older ones." <<He>> fleeces it down. "It has its own sort of appeal."
			<</if>>
			<br><br>

			<<if _gwylanStatus.includes("dom")>>
				<<He>> looks up at you and smiles. "Would you serve me in this, were I to ask?" <<He>> doesn't wait for you to answer.
			<</if>>
			<<He>> stands back up while gripping the skirt, <span class="pink">lifting the whole dress up over your head</span> along with your maid band. You barely even felt it happen.

		<<case "waiter" "waitress">>
			Gwylan walks around you, inspecting your $worn.upper.name.
			<<if $gwylan.request.special is "waitress">>
				"Well-pressed, good contrast to keep one's eyes high. The design on the front reminds one of an apron.<<if $gwylan_cafe_intro>> I bet you'd look cute in this while working at the cafe.<</if>>"
				<br><br>

				<<He>> suddenly crouches and lifts the short skirt, getting an unobstructed view of your <<undies>>. <<arousal 500>><<garousal>>
				<br>
				<<if $worn.under_lower.type.includes("naked")>>
					"Ah, a bold choice, letting yourself be exposed underneath. Lower rim is spacious, easy to move around in quickly. Breathable, too." <<npcincr Gwylan lust 1>><<glust>>
				<<else>>
					"Lower rim is spacious, easy to move around in quickly. Good for someone serving multiple clients at once."
				<</if>>
			<<else>>
				"Well-pressed, good contrast to keep one's eyes high. The waist apron is a cute touch.<<if $gwylan_cafe_intro>> I bet you'd look handsome in this while working at the cafe.<</if>>"
				<br>
				<<He>> suddenly yanks the apron forward, opening your trousers and getting an unobstructed view of your <<undies>>. <<arousal 500>><<garousal>>
				<<if $worn.under_lower.type.includes("naked")>>
					"Ah, a brave choice, letting yourself be exposed underneath. More loose than it looks. Breathable, too." <<npcincr Gwylan lust 1>><<glust>>
				<<else>>
					"Trousers are more spacious than they look. There's even a pouch behind the apron. Easy to move around in quickly. Good for someone serving multiple clients at once."
				<</if>>
			<</if>>
			<br><br>

			<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("butterfly_pea_flower_tea")>>
				<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique ("butterfly_pea_flower_tea")>><<set _noOptions to true>>
				<<if !$gwylanTea>>
					<<He>> looks up at you with a thoughtful expression on <<his>> face. "Say, do you happen to know how to make butterfly pea flower tea?"
					<br><br>

					You've never even heard of that before. You shake your head, prompting Gwylan to smile.
				<<else>>
					<<He>> looks up at you with a thoughtful expression on <<his>> face. "Say, I never did show you how to make butterfly pea flower tea, did I?"
					<br><br>

					<<if $gwylanTea gte 3>>
						You barely manage to suppress a groan. Gwylan smiles.
					<<else>>
						You shake your head, prompting Gwylan to smile.
					<</if>>
				<</if>>
				"Well, you're about to learn! No <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? "waiter" : "waitress">> in my shop can afford to live without such precious knowledge!"
				<<He>> vanishes in the back of the shop, and you hear some loud clinking for a few moments. <<He>> returns, balancing a tray laden with several herbs, a cup of freshly washed berries, a ladle, a patterned tea set and a glass pot of hot water.
				<br><br>

				<<link [[Next|Gwylan Request Clothes Waiter Tea]]>><</link>>
				<br>
			<<elseif _gwylanLovePercent gte 50 and C.npc.Gwylan.lust gte 25>>
				<<He>> looks up at you with a thoughtful expression on <<his>> face.
				<<if $worn.neck.collared is 1>>
					"You even brought a collar. You'd be ready to serve me," <<he>> says with a wink.
				<<else>>
					"All it's missing is a collar, and you'd be ready to serve me," <<he>> says with a wink.
				<</if>>
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<if !_noOptions>>
				Right after <<his>> comment, <<he>> <span class="pink"> pulls your
				<<if $gwylan.request.special is "waitress">>
					trousers fully down, and your shirt up and over your head.
				<<else>>
					uniform up and over your head.
				<</if>>
				</span>
			<</if>>

		<<case "nurse" "plastic nurse">>
			Gwylan inspects your nurse costume. "I don't think that's standard garb for actual nurses. At least, not anymore. The job of a nurse is hard enough without all the ogling that uniform could cause."
			<<if $gwylan.request.special is "plastic nurse">>
				<<He>> runs <<his>> hands along it, causing the plastic to lightly squeak. "Oh, that's awful. It must be easy to clean, though."
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<He>> smiles. "Still, it's better than being naked." With that, <<he>> grabs the rim of the skirt and <span class="pink">pulls the whole dress off over your head</span>, along with your nurse hat.
			<<if $gwylan.request.items.some(item => item.name === "nurse socks")>>
				Somehow, you feel even more exposed still wearing the nurse socks than if you were completely naked. You carefully take them off and hand them to Gwylan too, before <<he>> gets any ideas.
			<</if>>

		<<case "gothic">>
			<<set _noOptions to true>>
			Gwylan takes a step back to study your $worn.upper.name. <<He>> nods thoughtfully. "You look good. I'd like for you to keep this set. Very solemn. Like someone took a slice of midnight with a cookie cutter.
			It's not the most period-accurate representation, but it does remind one of the mourning dress of the Victorian era."
			<<He>> runs a hand over your sleeve. "Back then, they dipped clothes in arsenic to get that rich black. Deep and dark, for when you've lost the light of your life."
			<<He>> notices the look on your face and giggles. "Don't worry, dye methods have come a long way since then."
			<br><br>

			<<if $worn.head.name is "top hat">>
				"I'm sure you're familiar with mourning veils, but men had mourning attire as well. While the societal rules around proper dress were less stringent for them, they wore black coats and breeches."
				<<He>> takes your top hat off your head and measures the width of the band against <<his>> hand. "Many men tied a crepe sash around their hatband. Its width signaled their relationship with the deceased."
				<<He>> places it back on your head and adjusts it.
				<br><br>
			<<elseif $worn.upper.name.includes("gothic gown")>>
				"Women had particularly stringent societal rules around appropriate attire. Custom held that there were three mourning stages: first mourning, secondary mourning, and half mourning.
				There were plenty of rules around what kinds of fabrics and accoutrements were acceptable when." <<He>> nods at the bow on your dress.
				"For example, those bows and frills were acceptable for non-married women in first mourning, but not for widows. Their first mourning period was more intense, and was also referred to as deep mourning."
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<He>> circles around you, examining you from different angles. "There were general rules around the appropriate length of mourning. Widows who stopped wearing mourning dress too soon were thought to be sexually promiscuous!
			It's interesting, really. How long should someone wait before seeking out companionship? I suppose some would say you never should.
			The queen herself mourned her husband until her dying day, and never stopped wearing black. Romantic, or tragic? Who's to say. I'm sure people judged her for mourning too long."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> stops pacing. "It's funny, the expectations people have. As if you could simply flip a switch"—<<he>> snaps <<his>> fingers; one of the light bulbs above you goes dark—"and stop mourning.
			Grief doesn't work that way. And even when you've 'moved on'... it always, always comes back. Not always in the same form. Not always on the same shores. But those tides of grief will find their way back to you.
			Over and over and over again. Some days you can see it before it rolls in. Some days it crashes down when you least expect it. Some days it's enough to drown in."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> meets your gaze and gives you a smile. It's strangely distant and wooden. There's a lump in your throat. You're not sure why.
			<br><br>

			Before you can speak, Gwylan pipes back up. "Well!" <<he>> says. <<His>> voice is falsely chipper at first, but <<he>> quickly adjusts.
			<<He>> sounds much more at ease when <<he>> continues. "Now that I've brought down the mood... what can I do for you?"
			<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
			<br><br>

			<<gwylanOptions>>

		<<case "karate">>
			Gwylan examines your karate outfit.
			<<switch $worn.upper.accessory_colour>>
				<<case "black">>"Wow, a black belt? You must really know how to defend yourself," <<he>> chuckles.
				<<case "brown">>"A brown belt. A step before the final rank. Represents maturity, like a ripe fruit."
				<<case "red">>"A red belt. Sometimes represents the third highest ranking, but is sometimes swapped in place with purple."
				<<case "purple">>"A purple belt. Sometimes represents the third highest ranking, but is sometimes swapped in place with red."
				<<case "blue">>"A blue belt. Usually between purple and red in ranking. Can represent water and the fluidity of movement."
				<<case "green">>"A green belt, representing the growth of the student. The first steps of progress on a long road."
				<<case "tangerine">>"An orange belt. These aren't always used, but when they are, it's meant to show a continuation of the yellow belt rank. Like the sun setting, and the period of rest before a new day of learning."
				<<case "yellow">>"A yellow belt, the first step above white. Represents the fresh enlightenment of a novice."
				<<case "white">>"A white belt, representing the blank slate of a new student. Not a symbol of shame, but of potential."
				<<default>>"I don't think that belt colour is recognised as an official rank," <<he>> chuckles.
			<</switch>>
			<<He>> unties the belt, and opens the jacket slightly before playfully poking your belly. "I hope you don't mind if I have this."
			<<He>> doesn't wait for an answer, <span class="pink">pulling the jacket off of you before pulling the trousers down, too</span>.

		<<case "sailor">>
			Gwylan examines your sailor costume. "This town has a rich maritime history. You can't escape the salt in the air, even out here in the forest.
			Our docks are famed for being a staging ground for large operations during the second World War. Unfortunately, that also made them an enticing target for bombings."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> lifts the sailor hat from your head. "The ocean is the root of all life in the world. It is the origin point. We used to worship it as it fed and nurtured us. Then we began to use it for travel and trade. We began to exploit it.
			Finally, we used it for war. We spilled each other's blood in the water for eons. One must wonder just how many gallons of it. Do you think such a thing could even be measured?"
			<br><br>

			<<His>> expression is hard to read as <<he>> walks around you. <<His>> fingers brush your neck. "In beautiful displays of hatred, we sank each other's ships to the bottom, consigning the souls aboard to eternal rest in the waves, caring not for the debris we left behind.
			Do you think the sea would eventually inherit our hatred after drinking so much of our blood, and chewing up the bones of our ships? No.
			The rotten hulls become new ecosystems in and of themselves, and life blooms from death. The ocean always adapts. But... what if it couldn't anymore?"
			<br><br>

			<<He>> gently presses <<his>> palms against your chest. "The ocean remembers everything, despite its ever-shifting fluidity. The history of life itself lies within it.
			All water eventually returns to the tide, and all of us do, too. So why have we forgotten? Why do we take its boons for granted?"
			<br><br>

			Gwylan smiles. "Just something to think about. I appreciate you bringing this to me." <span class="pink"><<He>> pulls the shirt up over your head.</span>
		<<case "short sailor">>
			Gwylan examines your short sailor costume.
			<br><br>

			As <<he>> walks behind you, you feel something get draped around your neck. It's a white scarf, patterned like some kind of bird. It feels heavy.
			<br><br>

			<<He>> circles you, avoiding eye contact until <<he>> turns on <<his>> heel in front of you.
			"The tales of the sea and forest are closer together than you might think. To kill a bird of the sea, or to slay a mother fox, is to invite disaster.
			There are stories aplenty of these beasts leading lost travelers to safety, only to be killed in suspicion of bringing misfortune. Which, of course, is then brought on by their death. A terrible cycle."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> smiles. "In frustration, the companions of the one who dealt the killing blow would make them wear the beast about their neck as a mark of shame, a symbol of the burden.
			Today, we wear such symbols willingly. Some are oh so eager to keep digging once they reach the bottom." <span class="pink"><<He>> pulls the shirt and scarf up over your head.</span>

		<<case "football">>
			Gwylan gives your $worn.head.name a solid knock. You hardly feel anything. "We should use these in some of our own sports." <<He>> lifts it off of you after a brief struggle.
			<br><br>

			"We sure do love hurting each other, don't we? We even make entertainment out of it. At least we take the proper precautions. Occasionally. I'd like to examine the padding on the rest of the outfit, too. Do you mind?"
			<br><br>

			<span class="pink">You realise <<hes>> asking you to strip,</span> and comply.

		<<case "cheerleader">>
			Gwylan circles around you, inspecting your cheerleader outfit. "Morale is a powerful thing. Having people you know cheering for you can inspire one to feats of great strength. There's a sense of defending one's home territory and people."
			<br><br>

			You blink at Gwylan.
			<br><br>

			"What I'm trying to say is, cheerleading is a natural evolution of the war chant. I would argue it's more effective due to the sexual tension it invokes, too. Anyways, do you mind if I have this?"
			<<He>> doesn't wait for you to answer, and twirls you by your arm. <span class="pink">Your cheerleader top flies right off, and the skirt follows soon after.</span>

		<<case "cowboy">>
			Gwylan takes your cowboy hat, briefly putting it on. "Good style, but not shady enough for my tastes."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> walks around you, and swiftly <span class="pink">yanks down your chaps</span>.

		<<case "bunny">>
			<<set _noOptions to true>><<upperstrip>><<lowerstrip>>
			Gwylan flicks your bunny ears. "Sex appeal is a great way to get customers to dish out more money. Even if they're not consciously thinking of recompense, the chemistry of the brain is pushed towards it."
			<br><br>

			<<if $worn.upper.name isnot "naked" or $worn.lower.name isnot "naked">>
				<<He>> stares at you for a moment. You realise <<he>> can't exactly see the rest with your clothes in the way, and strip down to your leotard.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<link [[Next|Gwylan Request Clothes Bunny]]>><</link>>
			<br>

		<<case "kitty">>
			<<if $worn.upper.name isnot "naked" or $worn.lower.name isnot "naked">>
				You tell Gwylan that you're wearing the catgirl underwear. "Wonderful," <<he>> says. "May I see?"
				<br><br>

				You strip down to your underwear. Gwylan's gaze makes you feel entirely naked, though.
				<br><br>
			<</if>>

			<<if _gwylanStatus.includesAny("aroused", "lust")>>
				"I'll be honest with you," Gwylan starts. "I just wanted to see you dressed up like this. You look adorable." <<He>> pats you on the head.
			<<else>>
				"You pull off that look pretty well," <<he>> says with a giggle. "You look adorable." <<He>> pats you on the head.
			<</if>>
			"There's something appealing about it, isn't there? Taking on the features of something animalistic?
			<<if $cat gte 6>>
				I'm sure you feel right at home like this."
			<<elseif $fox gte 6 or $wolfgirl gte 6 or $cow gte 6>>
				I'm sure you agree."
			<<else>>
				I think you'd make a cute cat."
			<</if>>
			<<if _gwylanTF.tail is "revealed">>
				<<His>> tail flits around behind <<him>>.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>

			<<if _gwylanStatus.includesAny("dom", "lust")>>
				<<set _noOptions to true>><<upperstrip>><<lowerstrip>><<feetstrip>><<handheldstrip>><<facestrip>>

				<<He>> gets very close to you and caresses your cheek. "Does my little cat want a treat? Will you purr for me?" <<His>> touch sends a shiver of pleasure through your body. <<arousal 500>><<garousal>>
				<br><br>

				<<link [[Purr|Gwylan Request Clothes Kitty]]>><<set $phase to 1>><<transform cat 1>><</link>><<if $cat gte 6>><<cat>><<else>><<deviant1>><</if>>
				<br>
				<<link [[Nod|Gwylan Request Clothes Kitty]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
				<br>
				<<link [[Shake head|Gwylan Request Clothes Kitty]]>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>><<gwylanWillpowerDifficulty>>
				<br>
			<<else>>
				<<He>> walks behind you and <span class="pink">unclips your bra, before pulling down your panties</span>. "I'll be keeping these."
			<</if>>

		<<default>>
			<<if $gwylan.request.items.length gte 2>>
				Gwylan inspects the clothes you've brought. After a moment, <<he>> grabs you by the arm and twirls you,
				<span class="pink">removing your <<print formatList(_clothesToTakeText)>> in a blurred flurry.</span>
				"I'll be keeping these," <<he>> says.
			<<else>>
				Gwylan inspects the <<print $gwylan.request.items[0].name>>. <<He>> hums as <<he>> looks it over.
				Suddenly, <<he>>
				<<if $gwylan.request.items[0].slot is "head">>
					lifts it off of your head.
				<<else>>
					tugs. With minimal resistance, <span class="pink">it comes right off of your body</span>. You expect to hear a rip, but it seems completely intact.
				<</if>>
				"I'll be keeping this," <<he>> says.
			<</if>>
	<</switch>>

	<<if !_noOptions>>
		<br><br>

		<<for _cl to 0; _cl lt _clothesToTake.length; _cl++>>
			<<set _noRebuy to true>>
			<<generalRuined _clothesToTake[_cl]>>
		<</for>>
		<<if $exposed gte 1>>
			"Might as well buy a replacement while you're here!" <<He>> hands you some towels.
			<<towelup>>
		<</if>>
		"Thank you for bringing this to me. If there's anything you need, I'll be here."
		<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
		<br><br>

		<<gwylanOptions>>
	<</if>>
<</if>>

:: Gwylan Request Clothes Waiter Tea
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<He>> pours the hot water. "It's very simple, but you can't be careless. Butterfly pea flowers are very delicate. If you're not careful while steeping, they'll crumble in the water and ruin the flavour."
<<He>> shows you the proper technique, and you repeat it as best you can.
<br><br>

Your water turns a rich blue.
"Perfect! Give it a taste." You do so. It's different than any other kind of tea you've had before. Gwylan asks what you think of it.
<br><br>

<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"It's a bit earthy," you mumble.
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"It's like drinking lawn clippings," you say bluntly.
<<else>>
	"It tastes like grass," you remark with a shrug.
<</if>>
"Are you sure I did this right?"
<br><br>

<<He>> chuckles. "You did it perfectly. I'm aware it's an acquired taste," Gwylan acknowledges with a nod, sipping <<his>> own tea. "I've just had enough time to get used to it, that's all. The berries should help."
You give <<him>> a quizzical look, and <<he>> responds with an inscrutable smile. You shrug and take another sip. <<Hes>> right; the berries help.
<br><br>

"Now you're a proper <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? "waiter" : "waitress">>. Unfortunately, I need these."
As soon as you put your teacup down, <span class="pink">Gwylan strips you bare of your uniform</span> with two quick, precise pulls.
<br><br>

<<upperruined true>><<lowerruined true>>
"Might as well buy a replacement while you're here!" <<He>> hands you some towels.
<<towelup>>
"Thank you for bringing this to me. If there's anything you need, I'll be here."
<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Request Clothes Bunny
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

<<He>> walks behind you, and runs <<his>> hands up the leotard. <<Hes>> only inspecting the clothing, but your body responds to <<his>> prodding regardless. <<arousal 1000>><<garousal>>
<br><br>

You hear a zipper unzip, <span class="pink">and your leotard falls right off</span>. "Sorry, I couldn't get a good look with your body in the way." <<He>> lifts it from the ground.
<br><br>

<<underupperruined true>><<underlowerruined true>><<headruined true>>
<<if $gwylan.request.items.some(item => item.slot === "neck")>>
	<<neckruined true>>
<</if>>
<<clotheson>><<towelup>>
"Thank you for bringing these to me. If there's anything you need, I'll be here."
<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>

:: Gwylan Request Clothes Kitty
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>

<<if $phase is 1 or $phase is 2 or ($phase is 3 and $hypnosis_traits.devotion gte 1 and !$willpowerSuccess)>>
	<<if $phase is 3>>
		<<hypnosisText "There's a brief spark of resistance in you, <span class='red'>but it's washed away as Gwylan continues to pet you.</span>">> The urge is too much.
		<br><br>
	<</if>>
	<<if $phase is 1 or $phase is 3>>
		<<if $cat gte 6>>
			You purr just like a cat.
		<<else>>
			You do your best impression of a cat's purr.
		<</if>>
		"<<pcPetname "Gwylan" "good">>," Gwylan whispers.
	<<else>>
		You slowly nod your head.
	<</if>>
	Your heart begins to race as you wonder what 'treat' <<he>> has in mind.
	<<if $phase is 1 and $cat lt 6>>
		<<deviancy1>>
	<<else>>
		<br><br>
	<</if>>

	<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion gte 5 and $phase isnot 2>>
		"Oh, you poor thing," <<he>> coos. "You look like you can hardly wait." Your vision starts to get blurry, and shades of colour creep into your peripheral vision. "I won't make you wait, then."
		<br><br>

		<<hypnosisText "<<He>> snaps <<his>> fingers, and you're no longer where you once were.">>
		<br><br>

		<<link [[Next|Gwylan Cream Lick]]>><<set $worshipstart to 1>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
		<br>
	<<else>>
		<<His>> thumb touches the corner of your mouth. "Wait here." <<He>> briskly walks through a dark doorway.
		<<if _gwylanTF.tail is "revealed">>
			<<His>> tail swings back and forth rapidly as <<he>> leaves.
		<</if>>
		You hear the rustling of cloth, followed by the sound of compressed air and a dull thud. After a moment, you hear <<his>> voice again. "Alright. Here, kitty, kitty."
		<br><br>

		You walk to the doorway. The room is dark, and none of the light from outside seems to leak in. You take a cautious step forward. "Just follow my voice," <<he>> whispers from somewhere in the dark.
		You take another step towards <<him>>.
		<<if $worn.neck.collared is 1 and $worn.neck.type.includes("leash")>>
			Your leash starts to pull itself along the ground into the darkness. It suddenly goes taut, lightly pulling you in the same direction.
		<</if>>
		<br><br>

		<<link [[Follow|Gwylan Cream Lick]]>><<set $worshipstart to 1>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
		<br>
		<<link [[Turn around|Gwylan Cream Lick]]>><<set $worshipstart to 1>><<set $phase to 3>><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	You blink at Gwylan, before shaking your head. "You're no fun," <<he>> pouts. <<His>> arms wrap around you, and <<he>> unhooks your bra. "I'll be keeping these." <<He>> then pulls down your panties, too.
	<br><br>

	<<underupperruined true>><<underlowerruined true>><<headruined true>>
	<<if $gwylan.request.items.some(item => item.slot === "neck")>>
		<<neckruined true>>
	<</if>>
	<<clotheson>><<towelup>>
	"Thank you for bringing these to me. If there's anything you need, I'll be here."
	<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
	<br><br>

	<<gwylanOptions>>
<</if>>


:: Gwylan Request Ingredients Complete
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set _itemsDelivered to []>>
<<run $gwylan.request.items.forEach(item => {
	if (V.plants[item.name]) V.plants[item.name].amount -= item.need;
})>>
<<run $gwylan.request.items.forEach(item => _itemsDelivered.pushUnique(item.name))>>

You hand the ingredients over to Gwylan.
<br><br>

<<cleareventpool>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includesAny("red_rose", "white_rose")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_roses">>
		<<He>> smells the roses. "Lovely. You've picked some fine specimens."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("orchid")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_orchid">>
		"Wonderfully fiery pink colours on these orchids. You've picked them well."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("daisy")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_daisy">>
		"These are good daisies. Well done."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("tulip")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_tulip">>
		"I've always been nostalgic for tulips, although I wish I could remember why."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("lotus")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_lotus" 2>>
		"Oh, these lotus are wonderful." <<He>> gently cups them in <<his>> hands.
		"Did you know that our lake is named for them? Lake Whiteflower, for these beautiful floating blooms that grace the surface en masse."
		<<He>> pauses. "Well, that's not entirely true. The name is a mutation of the name of a now-extinct noble family, and that name roughly translated to 'little flower'."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("banana")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_banana">>
		"Pulped bananas really improve the texture and thickness of drinks. You can also make dairy-free ice cream out of them if you know what you're doing."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("lemon")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_lemon">>
		/* ToDo: Gwylan - Robin lemonade interaction, bringing lemonade to Gwylan at the cafe */
		<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("robin_lemonade_get")>>
			"Your friend Robin. <<nnpc_He "Robin">> puts a lot of care into that lemonade. It seems like such a small thing, but it's easy to tell."
		<<else>>
			<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("robin_lemonade")>>
			"There's this lemonade stand down by the beach," <<he>> starts. "I see it there from my table at the cafe every weekend. I always want to take a walk down there and buy some, but the beach... doesn't agree with me."
		<</if>>
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("blood_lemon")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_blood_lemon" 10>>
		"Blood lemons are a potent aphrodisiac, and a base for several reactive agents. You've done me a huge favour getting these."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("strawberry")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_strawberry">>
		"Every morning, strawberry crepes," <<he>> says. "Sammy picks a fruit to put alongside my crepes every morning, based on how <<nnpc_he "Sam">> thinks I'll be feeling that day. I'm almost always feeling 'strawberries', apparently."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("plum")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_plum" 2>>
		"I love plums," <<he>> says. "I wish I could do more with them. I tried making plum tea once, but it was a disaster."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("mushroom")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_mushroom">>
		"Heartshrooms," <<he>> says. "A minor stimulant, but not hallucinogenic. I can use these for a lot."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("wolfshroom")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_wolfshroom">>
		"I always need more wolfshrooms," <<he>> says. "They keep the wolves from breaking in. They have some other uses, too."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("ghostshroom")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_ghostshroom">>
		"Legends say ghostshrooms only sprout on the site of a great injustice or tragedy. I'm not sure about that, but what I do know is that they're a good palette cleanser. They also help flush foreign substances out of the body."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("wild_honeycomb")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_wild_honeycomb">>
		"Real honey is so hard to come by these days," <<he>> says. "Store-bought won't do me any good. Plus, the honeycombs themselves have uses, too."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("strange_flower")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_strange_flower">>
		"A curious little flower, isn't it?" <<He>> picks up a strange flower with a pair of tongs. "It's often refined into all manner of awful substances, but many useful ones, too."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("bird_egg")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_bird_egg">>
		<<He>> turns one of the bird eggs around in <<his>> hand. "Have you ever eaten one of these? They're quite tasty. They have a very distinct taste from chicken eggs.
		I only wish I didn't have to compete with the entire fox population for them. I suppose I didn't this time."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("plumeria")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_plumeria">>
		<<He>> smells the plumerias. "Oh, I've missed this smell. It's been ages since I could work with these."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("salt")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_salt" 0.8>>
		"Salt is useful for almost everything. Not just food or drink. Some say it can be used to ward away spirits and shear away bad luck."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("vegetable_oil")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_vegetable_oil" 0.8>>
		"Vegetable oil is a perfect base for many concoctions. It can be used as lubricant in a pinch too. I wouldn't recommend it, though."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includes("sugar")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_sugar" 0.8>>
		<<He>> sticks <<his>> finger in the sugar, pulls it out, and licks it. "What? You were thinking of doing it too, don't lie."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _itemsDelivered.includesAny("red_wine", "white_wine")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_wine" 0.8>>
		"Red and white, just like roses," <<he>> says as <<he>> picks up a bottle of wine. "Both red and white wine are perfect bases for many concoctions."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

/* ToDo: Gwylan - More ingredient flavour text */

<<addinlineevent "gwylan_ingredients_default" 0.1>>
	<<He>> begins sorting them by colour and weight.
<</addinlineevent>>

<<runeventpool>>

<<He>> smiles at you. "Thank you. Let me know if there's anything you need in return."
<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
<br><br>

<<gwylanOptions>>


:: Gwylan Request Sample
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("sample")>>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"Your measuring charms are all burnt up," you say to Gwylan.
		<<case "bratty">>
			"Your measuring charms are used up," you say to Gwylan.
		<<default>>
			"Your measuring charms have burned out," you say to Gwylan.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> nods. "I haven't had time to replace them, but you could help me.
<<else>>
	<<if $temple_confessor_intro and $gwylanTalked.includes("temple_confessor")>>
		<<switch $speech_attitude>>
			<<case "meek">>
				"You mentioned a... poison in the world," you start. "It sounds like what the bishop told me. How do you keep track of it?"
			<<case "bratty">>
				"You mentioned poison in the world," you start. "It sounds a lot like what the bishop told me. How do you track it?"
			<<default>>
				"You mentioned poison in the world," you start. "It sounds similar to what bishop told me. How do you keep track of it?"
		<</switch>>
	<<else>>
		<<switch $speech_attitude>>
			<<case "meek">>
				"You mentioned a... p-poison in the world," you start. "How do you keep track of it?"
			<<case "bratty">>
				"You rattled on about some kind of poison in the world," you start. "How do you keep track of it?"
			<<default>>
				"You mentioned something about poison in the world," you start. "Can you elaborate? How do you keep track of it?"
		<</switch>>
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> gives you a tired smile. "I'm glad you asked. I haven't had the time to set up my usual method of tracking it, but it's something you might be able to help me with.
<</if>>
<<if $gwylan.request.event>>
	I need you to <span class="blue">do what I already asked of you first</span>, though."
	<br><br>

	<<gwylanOptions>>
<<else>>
	If it's not too much trouble." <<He>> stands.
	<<run gwylanRequest("sample")>>
	<<set $gwylan.request.hold to "corruption">>
	<<set $gwylan.request.command to 1>>
	<<gwylanRequestText>>
	<br><br>

	<<gwylanOptions>>
<</if>>

:: Gwylan Request Sample Complete
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set _sampleSources to []>>
<<run $gwylan.request.items.forEach(sample => _sampleSources.pushUnique(sample.name))>>
You hand the vials over to Gwylan.
<br><br>

<<He>> smiles at you, and holds one up to the light.

<<cleareventpool>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("human")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_human_1">>
		"Humans aren't the only victims of this poison, but some spread it willingly."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_human_2">>
		"Humans have the potential to be the most unchecked source of the poison's spread. By the time one realises something is wrong with them, they've often already spread it to others, or back into the world itself."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_human_3">>
		"What have they been up to on Elk Street...?"
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("wolf")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_wolf_1">>
		"The spread is especially rapid between wolves. It amplifies aggression, which quickens spread, which further amplifies aggression. The tightly-knit pack doesn't help either."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_wolf_2">>
		<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("likes_wolves")>>
			"I hope you had fun running with your wolves."
		<<else>>
			"I hope the pack didn't give you too much trouble."
		<</if>>
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("wolves_known")>>
		<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_wolf_3">>
			"I hope your pack is in good health."
		<</addinlineevent>>
	<</if>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("fox")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_fox_1">>
		<<if _gwylanTF.ears is "revealed">>
			<<His>> fox ears twitch.
		<</if>>
		"Foxes are more sensitive to the poison than most. They either avoid it by instinct, or fall prey to it easier than any other."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_fox_2">>
		"I hope the foxes didn't give you too much of a run-around. Chasing them down is always a pain."
		<<if _gwylanTF.tail is "revealed">>
			<<His>> tail beats behind <<him>>. "Although, part of me enjoys the chase.<<if $fox gte 6>> I'm sure you understand.<</if>>"
		<</if>>
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("cat")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_cat_1">>
		"Large cats are most often exposed by accident. Curiosity and all that. I can relate."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_cat_2">>
		"Let's see if the cats have been licking up anything they shouldn't be."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("lizard")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_lizard_1">>
		"Reptiles see the most intense changes to their physiology when overexposed to the poison. I've yet to figure out why."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_lizard_2">>
		"Overexposure to the poison leads to some interesting changes in reptiles. Pigmentation in the eyes is a common one. It makes their gaze unsettling, sometimes paralysing."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("dog")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_dog_1">>
		"As man's best friend, dogs are a common vector for transmission. Usually by accident."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_dog_2">>
		"Dogs are one of the easiest animals to influence thanks to selective breeding. Those with intentions pure and ill alike exploit them."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("boar")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_boar_1">>
		"Boars are very temperamental beasts. Luckily we don't have razorbacks here. Their heightened aggression would be a disaster for the ecosystem."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_boar_2">>
		"Boars had to be manually reintroduced to the ecosystem after being hunted to extinction. We sure have a knack for that."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("dolphin")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_dolphin_1">>
		"Dolphins are very problematic when it comes to spreading the poison. Cetaceans are vulnerable as it is, but dolphins almost seem to spread it on porpoise with how often they..."
		<<he>> stops <<himself>>. "That wasn't even on <i>purpose</i>, sorry."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_dolphin_2">>
		"Sexual promiscuity amidst dolphins would lead to rapid spread were the poison to become uncontrolled in the ocean."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_dolphin_3">>
		"All returns to the tide eventually," <<he>> whispers.
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("bear")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_bear_1">>
		"I'm terribly sorry for making you collect samples from bears, but I knew you'd come out alright."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_bear_2">>
		"Bears were once resistant to the taint. Let's hope that remains true."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.includes("plant")>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_plant_1">>
		"Nectar is a sexual fluid too, and thus holds the same traces when the poison passes through."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_plant_2">>
		"Animals aren't the only vector for the poison to spread. The very earth is vulnerable."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_plant_3">>
		"It's hard to know how the dryads feel about anything serious like this. They're always so mischievous and whimsical."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

<<if _sampleSources.length gte 4>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_variety_1">>
		"This is a good range of samples. It should tell me much."
	<</addinlineevent>>
	<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_variety_2">>
		"I hope it wasn't too much trouble to run around collecting all of these."
	<</addinlineevent>>
<</if>>

/* ToDo: Gwylan - more unique sample comments, make comments more likely based on number of matching samples */

<<addinlineevent "gwylan_sample_default" 0.5>>
	"The poison isn't spread through sexual fluid alone, but it always leaves traces behind in it."
<</addinlineevent>>

<<runeventpool>>
<br><br>

<<if $gwylan.request.hold is "corruption" and !$gwylan.requestDone>>
	<<He>> organises the vials on a countertop. "I'll use these right away. Thank you."
	<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
	<<set $gwylan.requestDone to false>>
<<else>>
	<<He>> organises the vials on a countertop. "I'll use these right away. Thank you. If you need anything in return, just say the word."
	<<gwylanRequestEnd>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("sample")>>
	<<He>> disappears through a dark doorway, but keeps talking. "As a reminder, once I'm done, these should last for about <span class="blue">two weeks</span>. I'll leave them in the open, so you can see them even if I'm not here."
